    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, slice the <strong>chicken thigh fillets</strong> into thin strips&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Deseed the<strong> yellow pepper<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into thin strips</p>\r\n<p>Dice the <strong>tomatoes</strong> finely</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/497__-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/497__-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/497__-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/497__-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/497__-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the pan with a drizzle of&nbsp;<strong>olive oil&nbsp;</strong>to a medium-high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the&nbsp;<strong>chicken strips</strong>&nbsp;and cook for 2 min</p>\r\n<p>Add the<strong>&nbsp;</strong><strong>ras el hanout</strong>,<strong> chopped tomato </strong>and&nbsp;<strong>yellow pepper</strong>&nbsp;and cook&nbsp;for a further 2 min or until&nbsp;beginning to brown</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/497__-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
